<title type="html"><![CDATA[Traits of the Salafi Manhaj]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1373&amp;p=1457#p1457"><![CDATA[
(1) – 1st Distinctive Trait of the Salafi Manhaj in Dawah – Dawah is for Allah Alone<br />(2) – 2nd Distinctive Trait of the Salafi Manhaj in Dawah – The Priorities of the Manhaj of Dawah must be clear to the Da’ee<br />(3) – 3rd Distinctive Trait of the Salafi Manhaj in Dawah – Adhering to Ittiba (obedience) and refraining from Ibtida (innovation)<br />(4) – 4th Distinctive Trait of the Salafi Manhaj in Dawah – Tarbiyah with ‘ilm (knowledge)<br />(5) – 5th Distinctive Trait of the Salafi Manhaj in Dawah – Giving Importance to The Arabic Language<br />(6) – 6th Distinctive Trait of the Salafi Manhaj in Dawah – Academic Discipline<br />The Da’ee must be confident that he is academically well-acquainted with what he is calling to.<br />The Da’ee must know the Akhlaaq (praiseworthy manners) of a Da’ee<br />The Da’ee must have Prudence in handling the affairs of the people<br />(7) 7th Distinctive Trait of the Salafi Manhaj in Dawah – Callers to Jamaa’ah (unity) and to abandonment of disunity<br />(8) – 8th Distinctive Trait of the Salafi Manhaj in Dawah – Moderation: (al-wasatiyyah and al-a’tidal)<br />(9) – 9th Distinctive Trait of the Salafi Manhaj in Dawah – Salafi Manhaj is founded upon the fundamentals derived from the Sharee’ah texts<br />Explaining the fundamental, ‘Considering the wider MaslaHa over the restricted MaslaHa’<br />Explaining the Fundamental, ‘Blocking the Means (that lead to evil)’<br />(10) – 10th Distinctive Trait of the Salafi Manhaj in Dawah – A Da’ee should spread Optimism<br />(11) – 11th Distinctive Trait of the Salafi Manhaj in Dawah – Refuting the doubts (that are raised) in the Deen<br />(12) – 12th Distinctive Trait of the Salafi Manhaj in Dawah – Guarding the Tongue from slandering the scholars<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2024">Abu Shaqran Zahiri</a> — Sat Mar 25, 2017 8:30 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
